 Abstract 
 (even though there is the existence of) the wider application of (wasting very little while working or producing something) analysis in Indian farming, little has been done on the (act of asking questions and trying to find the truth about something) of intra and 
 interecological differences/different versions, size differences and their interactions. However, (related to surrounding conditions or the health of the Earth) issues have most important effects/results/suggestions for the low-input 
 (able to last/helping the planet) farming-based production. What's more, due to the different causes of (wasting very little while working or producing something), the old size-based debate on (wasting very little while working or producing something) 
 differences is not yet resolved. The present study examines the level of technical (wasting very little while working or producing something) across (related to surrounding conditions or the health of the Earth) zones and farm size groups in 
 paddy farms of the southern Indian state of Tamil Nadu. The study showed that 90% of the difference/different version in output among paddy (IR-20) farms 
 ' in the state is due to differences in technical (wasting very little while working or producing something). Land, animal power and fertilisers have big influence on the level of paddy 
 production. Changing/different from 0.59 to 0.97, the mean technical (wasting very little while working or producing something) was found to be 0.83. The use of F-test in two-way analysis of 
 variance (ANOV A) and changed moving backward (Tobit model), with dummies for (related to surrounding conditions or the health of the Earth) zones, farm size groups and their interactions, has 
 shown that, at mean level, the level of technical (wasting very little while working or producing something) among paddy farms of the state differs significantly across agro-(related to surrounding conditions or the health of the Earth) zones 
 and size groups also. The study further pointed to/showed that small-sized paddy farms in zone II and medium-sized paddy farms in zone III are 
 represented by (related to surrounding conditions or the health of the Earth)ly size-(created unfair thinking in)/(unfair-thinking) production ways of doing things; this way (accomplishing or gaining) higher technical (wasting very little while working or producing something). Â© 1997 Elsevier Science B.V. 
 
 1. Introduction 
 
 The measurement of (wasting very little while working or producing something) (technical, allocative and money-based) has remained an area of important research both in the developed and developing 
 countries. Especially in developing farming-based 
 (processes of people making, selling, and buying things), where useful things/valuable supplies are poor/not enough and opportunities for developing and putting into use better technologies are reducing, (Ali and Chaudhry, 1990) (wasting very little while working or producing something) measurement is very important because it is a 
 factor for working well growth. Such studies help 
 
