 model were able to explain 96% of the difference/different version in 
 paddy production for the state. The coefficients of 
 land, labour, animal power and (material that makes plants grow better)s were highly 
 significant, but animal power has an unexpected 
 sign. This is because, in many of the 
 farms, own little bulls, for which the farmer pays no 
 hiring charge, are available. Because of this, given the (almost nothing/very little) opportunity cost of own little bulls, it is likely that 
 animal power could be overused. (in almost the same way), the coef- 
 
